    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Your mastery as a rider becomes apparent. You have Advantage on Saving Throws made to avoid falling off your mount. If you fall off your mount and descend no more than 10 feet, you can land on your feet if you do not have the &amp;Reference[Incapacitated apply=false] condition.</p><p>Additionally, mounting or dismounting a creature costs you only 5 feet of movement, rather than half your Speed.</p><p>Finally, your Maneuvers that affect you can be applied to your mount.</p>",
